[SN]TITLE[SN]
Action from Fort William Mountain Bike World Cup

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
All images are copyrighted.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Fort William Mountain Bike World Cup and Buff 4X Pro Tour were held at Nevis Range at the weekend.
Hundreds of riders competed in the events watched by a total of more than 20,000 spectators over two days.
The Fort William competition forms the third stage of the UCI World Cup Downhill championships.
Photographer Paul Campbell captured the action.
